{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Only files changed in the pull request are analyzed — unchanged files are not scanned.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"A pure unit test of file-filter logic can miss real failures in how PR file lists are fetched/paginated and passed into the analyzer. The failure boundary is module wiring: change detection + scan scheduler + analyzer input selection.","test_description":"Create a local integration harness with a repo fixture containing changed and unchanged files across a synthetic PR diff. Run the pipeline step components together (diff collector + file selector + analyzer dispatcher) and assert only changed paths are sent to analysis.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Findings are grouped by severity (error, warning, info) in the posted PR comment.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The risk is not just formatting logic; it is correct mapping from analyzer findings into grouped comment sections and outgoing comment payload construction. A unit test of formatter alone may miss schema/wiring mismatches.","test_description":"Run analyzer-output parsing, severity bucketing, and comment-body builder together with fixture findings containing mixed severities. Verify the generated PR comment payload contains distinct error/warning/info groups with correct membership.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A pull request that touches 200 files completes analysis within the 10-minute Actions timeout.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This is an end-to-end runtime/SLO behavior tied to subprocess execution, filesystem throughput, and CI runner constraints. Mocked or in-process tests can hide timeout and resource contention failures.","test_description":"Execute the actual lint step as a subprocess in a CI-like environment against a generated 200-file PR fixture, measure wall-clock completion, and fail if total duration exceeds 10 minutes (with artifact/log capture for bottleneck diagnosis).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.88,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When the linter process crashes on a malformed file, the remaining files are still analyzed and results posted.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Crash resilience depends on real subprocess failure semantics (exit codes/signals/partial output) and recovery logic. Mocking linter calls can easily hide true crash-handling defects.","test_description":"Use a real linter subprocess with one malformed file that triggers a crash/fatal error for that invocation. Run the pipeline executor over multiple files and assert subsequent files are still processed and a final PR comment is produced with surviving findings plus crash note.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.17,"System":0.78,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Duplicate findings on the same line from overlapping rules are deduplicated in the output.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Dedup often fails at the boundary between rule engine output normalization and final rendering (key construction, path/line normalization, rule IDs). A unit test of a dedup helper may miss upstream shape inconsistencies.","test_description":"Feed fixture analyzer results from multiple overlapping rules through normalization + dedup + comment rendering pipeline, including same-path/line duplicates with slight metadata differences, and assert only one output entry per dedup key appears.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
